Just to clear things up.. the file I&#39;m referring to is not from anyone
involved in this group so when I say that occasionally I hear their
voices become shaky, that is not a comment on anyone here. Also,
please don&#39;t misread what I actually said. The point I made, or tried
to make, about the investigators not hearing what I heard... I
wouldn&#39;t have heard all of it in real time either. Too many layers,
too fast, etc. I have the luxury now of sitting and analyzing the file
in my own time. 

As for fear being a factor... I do believe that the attitude of the
investigators present during a session does effect the outcome. Even
Bruce who would rather cut my eyeballs out with a razor has said the
same. If you think that I am scared, fine. If I&#39;m missing one thing it
is probably a healthy dose of fear. Don&#39;t make the mistake of missing
the points by name calling. 

I post my thoughts here because it is an active group of people
working with this form of ITC. You can call me a shit stirrer or
whatever you want. The point is that I see issues that could be
addressed fairly easily. You can ignore it or deflect all you want.
For me, it&#39;s not about being friends, it&#39;s about the research.  


